WEBVTT

00:02.815 --> 00:04.597
about killer asteroids and comets? I would beware 
of spending an awful lot of money on killer

00:06.680 --> 00:13.950
asteroid and comet detection. I don't think 
that's appropriate. I think we as a scientific

00:17.034 --> 00:25.105
community should avoid raising the scare. This 
will always happen, however. I mean, look at the

00:28.470 --> 00:31.033
1910 comet. situation, and you've got an 
analogous situation. These things develop of

00:39.866 --> 00:52.787
their own accord, and in these tight funding 
times, it's awfully hard to fault the people who

00:39.866 --> 00:52.787
stand ready to prey on the public's fears. But I 
think as responsible scientists, we can do

00:52.807 --> 00:57.915
something. I would hope that we could keep the 
expenditures on these things to within

00:58.300 --> 01:06.507
reasonable and appropriate limits.

