13:41.152 --> 13:44.481
box. We had several gray boxes around us to various 
heights to reach the eyepiece. This gray box was

13:51.118 --> 13:57.895
perched on the waist-high observing ladder 
railing so that the railing itself was 10 feet over

13:58.280 --> 14:02.127
the floor. He had this foot and a half high box, and 
he was standing on tiptoes as this object he was

14:02.467 --> 14:13.546
looking was setting down into the pine trees on the 
west. Well, of course, he was doing one of these

14:13.566 --> 14:23.443
Rube Goldberg things one time and fell off it and 
broke his ribs rather badly. I guess one of many

14:24.335 --> 14:28.299
astronomers who've had accidents like that. This 
was before your time, of course, but were there any

